{
  "name": "Blight",
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Necrotic energy washes over a creature of your choice that you can see within range, draining moisture and vitality from it. The target takes 8d8 points of void damage. Creatures whose bodies contain no significant moisture (such as constructs) are immune to <em>blight</em>.</p>\n<p>If you target a creature made of water or a plant creature, use the outcome for one degree of success worse than the result of their saving throw, and the spell deals maximum damage to it. If you target a plant that isn't a creature, such as a tree or shrub, it doesn't make a saving throw; it simply withers and dies.</p>"
    },
